The paper discusses the modeling of complex systems as dynamic graphs, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on the emergence of global properties from local interactions between entities, which is a common theme in network science. The second likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the management and processing of graphs, which is a core topic in this field. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the dynamics of complex systems and their evolution over time. The fourth likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), as the paper discusses the modeling of complex systems in various domains, including biology, economy, and physics. The fifth likely category is cs.GR (Graphics), as the paper discusses the display of graphs and their visualization.
